    "treatments": "Treatment for stable angina focuses on reducing symptoms and preventing complications. Lifestyle changes such as adopting a heart-healthy diet, engaging in regular exercise, and quitting smoking are foundational steps. Medications like nitrates can help relieve angina symptoms during episodes, while beta-blockers and calcium channel blockers may be prescribed to help manage the condition more effectively. In some cases, angioplasty or coronary artery bypass grafting (CABG) may be recommended to improve blood flow to the heart. Regular follow-up with a healthcare provider is essential for monitoring the condition and adjusting treatment as necessary."
